Deleting Your Aura Account:
You may delete and cancel your Aura Account and your access to the Services at any time by contacting Aura at the phone number or email address below and requesting that your account and the associated photos be deleted. Doing so will remove your photos from our servers and from any frames to which you have contributed them. Please note that merely deleting the Aura mobile application from your phone or tablet will not delete your photos from the Services and will not cancel your Aura Account. Once you request account deletion, we will no longer store or use your content or information. Please further note that certain information and content may persist for some time in caching, backup, and archival copies and in our internal records relating to use of our Services.
Aura provides a print subscription service called Aura Analog, which may be purchased separately from our digital frames. When you subscribe to Aura Analog, you pay upfront for three months of service (by way of example, with monthly service priced at $7.99, you will pay 3 x $7.99 or $23.97 total upfront), plus any applicable sales tax. Aura will immediately send you a free Analog frame to hold your prints.
After your purchase, you will receive an email that provides instructions for signing up for the print subscription service. You should enter your own mailing address if you want the prints sent to you, or the address of a person to whom you’re planning to give the frame if you’d like them to receive the prints on an ongoing basis.
When you pay for the initial period of the subscription, Aura will store your credit card information to be used for recurring billing of the subscription.
Each month Aura will select five photos to be printed. You can accept those photos or substitute other photos from your collection or from photos that have been added to the frame by other contributors. The first set of five photos will be sent by Aura immediately after frame activation and your approval of the prints in the Aura app. Each additional set of five photos will then be sent on the one-month anniversary of the initial set of prints.
After your initial period (usually three months), Aura will charge you $7.99 each month on or about the date that the latest prints are sent out. You can cancel your subscription at any time by using the Aura app or visiting
https://auraframes.com/
.
If you give the frame as a gift, you can continue to select the prints each month and pay for the monthly subscription on an ongoing basis. However, you can also transfer the subscription (including either or both of the photo-selection process and the payment method) to another Aura user. To do that visit
https://auraframes.com/
.
For answers to questions about the Analog subscription service visit
https://help.auraframes.com/hc/articles/360050180353
.
The Aura Analog Frame is only available for purchase in the United States.
